[Matthew 28:9](../../../bib/kjv/mat028.htm#009.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_009">mat 28:9</span></span>

Jesus

The order of our Lord's appearances would seem to be:

On the day of his resurrection:

\(1\) To Mary Magdalene ([Joh
10:14-18](../../../bib/kjv/joh010.htm#014).md).

\(2\) To the women returning from the tomb with angelic message ([Mat
28:8-10](../../../bib/kjv/mat028.htm#008).md).

\(3\) To Peter, probably in the afternoon ([Luk
24:34](../../../bib/kjv/luk024.htm#034).md); ([Co1
15:5](../../../bib/kjv/co1015.htm#005).md).

\(4\) To the Emmaus disciples toward evening ([Luk
24:13-31](../../../bib/kjv/luk024.htm#013).md).

\(5\) To the apostles, except Thomas ([Luk
24:36-43](../../../bib/kjv/luk024.htm#036).md); ([Joh
20:19-24](../../../bib/kjv/joh020.htm#019).md).

Eight days afterward:

\(1\) to the apostles, Thomas being present ([Joh
20:24-29](../../../bib/kjv/joh020.htm#024).md).

In Galilee:

(1a) To the seven by the Lake of Tiberias ([Joh
21:1-23](../../../bib/kjv/joh021.htm#001).md).

\(2\) On a mountain, to the apostles and five hundred brethren ([Co1
15:6](../../../bib/kjv/co1015.htm#006).md).

At Jerusalem and Bethany again:

\(1\) To James ([Co1 15:7](../../../bib/kjv/co1015.htm#007).md).

\(2\) To the eleven ([Mat 28:16-20](../../../bib/kjv/mat028.htm#016).md);
([Mar 16:14-20](../../../bib/kjv/mar016.htm#014).md); ([Luk
24:33-53](../../../bib/kjv/luk024.htm#033).md); ([Act
1:3-12](../../../bib/kjv/act001.htm#003).md).

To Paul:

\(1\) Near Damascus ([Act 9:3-6](../../../bib/kjv/act009.htm#003).md);
([Co1 15:8](../../../bib/kjv/co1015.htm#008).md).

\(2\) In the temple ([Act 22:17-21](../../../bib/kjv/act022.htm#017).md);
([Act 23:11](../../../bib/kjv/act023.htm#011).md).

To Stephen: outside Jerusalem ([Act
7:55](../../../bib/kjv/act007.htm#055).md).

To John: on Patmos ([Rev 1:10-19](../../../bib/kjv/rev001.htm#010).md).

[Matthew 28:19](../../../bib/kjv/mat028.htm#019.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_019">mat 28:19</span></span>

Go

With the death and resurrection of Jesus Christ begins the "dispensation
of the grace of God" ([Eph 3:2](../../../bib/kjv/eph003.htm#002).md); which
is defined as "his kindness toward us through Christ Jesus"; and, "the
gift of God: not of works, lest any man should boast." ([Eph
2:7-9](../../../bib/kjv/eph002.htm#007).md); under grace God freely gives
to the believing sinner eternal life ([Rom
6:23](../../../bib/kjv/rom006.htm#023).md) accounts to him a perfect
righteousness; ([Rom 3:21](../../../bib/kjv/rom003.htm#021).md); ([Rom
3:22](../../../bib/kjv/rom003.htm#022).md); ([Rom
4:4](../../../bib/kjv/rom004.htm#004).md); ([Rom
4:5](../../../bib/kjv/rom004.htm#005).md) and accords to him a perfect
position ([Eph 1:6](../../../bib/kjv/eph001.htm#006).md).

The predicted results of this sixth testing of man are

\(1\) the salvation of all who believe ([Act
16:31](../../../bib/kjv/act016.htm#031).md).

\(2\) judgment upon an unbelieving world and an apostate church. ([Mat
25:31-46](../../../bib/kjv/mat025.htm#031).md); ([Th2
1:7-10](../../../bib/kjv/th2001.htm#007).md); ([Pe1
4:17](../../../bib/kjv/pe1004.htm#017).md); ([Pe1
4:18](../../../bib/kjv/pe1004.htm#018).md); ([Rev
3:15](../../../bib/kjv/rev003.htm#015).md); ([Rev
3:16](../../../bib/kjv/rev003.htm#016).md).

